    "body": "### Problem\n\nSemantic token highlighting fails when using tinymist with error\r\n```\r\nError executing vim.schedule lua callback: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/semantic_tokens.lua:304: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/semantic_tokens.lua:149: index\r\n out of range                                                                                                                                                             \r\nstack traceback:                                                                                                                                                          \r\n        [builtin#36]: at 0x7a4e388484e0                                                                                                                                   \r\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/semantic_tokens.lua:304: in function 'handler'                                                                                \r\n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:687: in function ''                                                                                                \r\n        vim/_editor.lua: in function <vim/_editor.lua:0>   \r\n```\r\nThe errors was introduced by the new 0.10.2 version, likely an off by one error\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/79c3ec8d-8cf5-485d-84e1-b799de6811d4)\r\non 0.11.0-dev it has highlighting, but they ain't coming from the LSP\n\n### Steps to reproduce using \"nvim -u minimal_init.lua\"\n\n```lua\r\nvim.lsp.set_log_level(\"debug\")\r\n\r\nlocal pattern = 'typst'\r\nlocal cmd = { 'tinymist' }\r\n-- Add files/folders here that indicate the root of a project\r\nlocal root_markers = { '.git', '.editorconfig', 'typst.toml' }\r\n-- Change to table with settings if required\r\nlocal settings = vim.empty_dict()\r\n\r\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('FileType', {\r\n\tpattern = pattern,\r\n\tcallback = function(args)\r\n\t\tlocal match = vim.fs.find(root_markers, { path = args.file, upward = true })[1]\r\n\t\tlocal root_dir = match and vim.fn.fnamemodify(match, ':p:h') or nil\r\n\t\tvim.lsp.start({\r\n\t\t\tname = 'bugged-ls',\r\n\t\t\tcmd = cmd,\r\n\t\t\troot_dir = root_dir,\r\n\t\t\tsettings = settings,\r\n\t\t})\r\n\tend,\r\n})\r\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe text should be highlighted with the proper LSP tokens, for keywords, strings, functions and so on\r\n![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/84fbbcc8-6824-412c-9b9f-115af0003ac5)\r\n\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.2 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1713484068 Run \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n\n### Language server name/version\n\ntinymist v0.11.28\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux x86_64\n\n### Log file\n\nhttps://gist.github.com/C0deBr3ak3r/129eb416ab046490b1a529d7a50b6142",
