            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Can we show an error like \"failed to decode server response, expected utf-x\"\r\n\r\nI don't think so, as we only receive an integer index from the LSP.\r\n\r\nInterestingly, I just backported #30585 to 0.10 and there is no error and the highlighting would continue to work, although this relies on the lua implementation of ```str_byteindex``` which we decided against in the blocking PR\r\n\r\nThis would still throw in the C implementation\r\n```lua\r\nlocal str = \"é\"\r\nprint(#str)\r\nprint(vim.str_byteindex(str, 2))\r\n```\r\nI cant think how we could bounds check it as #str is 2, so it passes for ```index < #str```",
