            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Similar errors encountered with plugins that allow switching buffers quickly e.g. Glance.nvim, oil.nvim\n\n```\nError executing vim.schedule lua callback: ...local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/semantic_tokens.lua:309: ...local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/semantic_tokens.lua:102: Invalid buffer id: 32\nstack traceback:\n\t[builtin#36]: at 0x5a9e035cf470\n\t...local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/semantic_tokens.lua:309: in function 'handler'\n\t/usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:687: in function ''\n\tvim/_editor.lua: in function <vim/_editor.lua:0>\nError executing vim.schedule lua callback: ...local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/semantic_tokens.lua:309: ...local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/semantic_tokens.lua:102: Invalid buffer id: 33\nstack traceback:\n\t[builtin#36]: at 0x5a9e035cf470\n\t...local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/semantic_tokens.lua:309: in function 'handler'\n\t/usr/local/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:687: in function ''\n\tvim/_editor.lua: in function <vim/_editor.lua:0>\n```\n\n[#435](https://github.com/stevearc/oil.nvim/issues/435) reported  in a plugin repo.\n\n\nI'm modifying with `pcall(api.nvim_buf_get_lines, bufnr, 0, -1, false)` in `semantic_tokens.lua` on the failing line to bypass for now. e.g.\n\n```lua\n-- semantic_tokens.lua:102\nlocal lines_success, lines = pcall(api.nvim_buf_get_lines, bufnr, 0, -1, false)\n\nif not lines_success then\n  return {}\nend\n\n```\n\nAlternatively. – a desperate overkill – disabling semantic tokens from LSP in my lspconfig when I have nvim-treesitter for syntax highlighting:\n\n```lua\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd(\"LspAttach\", {\n  callback = function(args)\n    local client = vim.lsp.get_client_by_id(args.data.client_id)\n    client.server_capabilities.semanticTokensProvider = nil\n end,\n})\n```",
